  <section id="soppel">
    <h2>Waste and Household</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Waste:There is two containers by the entrance to the property</li>
      <li>Sorting: General waste goes in the green container. The blue container is for carboard and paper. If you like to help me resirculate plastic please leave it in the open room between the house and the garage.</li>
      <li>Washing machine: The washingroom is in the room just below the stairs. It has a washing machine and a dryer. As the signs and info is in Norwegian I have made a video to show how to use it here: https://photos.app.goo.gl/7dXXUfak1Q34etos6 </li>
      <li>Dishwasher: There are two in the main floor, and one in the downstairs appartment</li>
      <li>Air conditioning: Use the white remote on the wall close to the AC unit. Use "mode" to select heating (shows a sun symbol), fan (fan symbol) or cooling (ice symbol), select fan speed to select if you would like to adjust the speed. Regulate the temperature with the "+" and "-" symbol </li>
      <li>Vacuum and cleaning supplies: There are several vacuum cleaners - a battery driven one is on the side of the kitchen towards the window, a vacuum cleaner with power below the stairs or in the washing room, and there is also one in the appartment. For cleaning supplies there are some in the kitchen door closest to the entrance as well as in the washingroom downstairs</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="tips">
    <h2>Things to do in Bergen</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fløyen:</strong> Amazing view – take the Fløibanen or hike up</li>
      <li><strong>Ulriken:</strong> Highest mountain in Bergen – take the cable car or hike the trail</li>
      <li><strong>Fish Market:</strong> Local food and seafood – best during the day</li>
      <li><strong>KODE Museums:</strong> Art and culture in the city center</li>
      <li><strong>Bryggen:</strong> UNESCO heritage site, historic wooden buildings and charming alleys</li>
      <li><strong>Restaurants:</strong> Try Lysverket, Colonialen, or Bare Vestland</li>
      <li><strong>Cafés:</strong> Kaffemisjonen, Blom, or Det Lille Kaffekompaniet</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="utsjekk">
    <h2>Check-out</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Check-out before 11:00 AM if an individual agreement is not made prior. I try to be flexible if there is no other guests comming the same day.</li>
      <li>Take out the trash and sort into the correct containers</li>
      <li>Start the dishwasher before you leave</li>
      <li>If you can turn off the lights that is great</li>
      <li>Double-check you’ve packed everything (closets, bathroom, fridge)</li>
      <li>Lock the doors</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

